"{\"abstract\":\"Epistemic negation not along with default negation \\u00ac plays a key role in knowledge representation and nonmonotonic reasoning. However, the existing approaches behave not satisfactorily in that they suffer from the problems of unintended world views due to recursion through the epistemic modal operator K or M (KF and MF are shorthands for \\u00acnotF and not\\u00acF , respectively). In this paper we present a general approach to epistemic negation which is free of unintended world views and thus offers a solution to the long-standing problem of epistemic specifications which were introduced by [Gelfond, 1991] over two decades ago.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1744468\",\"name\":\"Y. Shen\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1744468\"},{\"authorId\":\"72431510\",\"name\":\"Thomas Eiter\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/72431510\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"1907.09247\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1898535\",\"name\":\"Jorge Fandinno\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1017/S1471068419000127\",\"intent\":[\"background\",\"result\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"affb08199d3f49d32bcd4b6edfc1684ef9f1aa6a\",\"title\":\"Founded (Auto)Epistemic Equilibrium Logic Satisfies Epistemic Splitting\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/affb08199d3f49d32bcd4b6edfc1684ef9f1aa6a\",\"venue\":\"Theory Pract. Log. Program.\",\"year\":2019},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2021768\",\"name\":\"Pedro Cabalar\"},{\"authorId\":\"1898535\",\"name\":\"Jorge Fandinno\"},{\"authorId\":\"2239039\",\"name\":\"L. Cerro\"}],\"doi\":\"10.24963/ijcai.2020/653\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"c0e4d905532bb2ec5d7440ba0620236815b49250\",\"title\":\"On the Splitting Property for Epistemic Logic Programs (Extended Abstract)\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/c0e4d905532bb2ec5d7440ba0620236815b49250\",\"venue\":\"IJCAI\",\"year\":2020},{\"arxiv